# Common Patterns

## GUI Applications
- Use `QApplication`.
- Document X11 prerequisites in README.
- Provide macOS (`DISPLAY=host.docker.internal:0`) and Linux (`-v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix`) run examples.
- Suppress GL noise: `-e QT_LOGGING_RULES="*.debug=false;qt.qpa.*=false"`.

## Console Applications
- Use `QCoreApplication`.
- No X11 instructions necessary.
- Provide streamlined run commands.

## CMake Template
```cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.16)
project(lesson-name VERSION 1.0 LANGUAGES CXX)

set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 17)
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD_REQUIRED ON)
set(CMAKE_AUTOMOC ON)

find_package(Qt6 COMPONENTS Core Widgets REQUIRED)

add_executable(executable-name main.cpp)
target_link_libraries(executable-name PRIVATE Qt6::Core Qt6::Widgets)

install(TARGETS executable-name RUNTIME DESTINATION /opt/lesson##)
```
